<p>I got a function like that</p>  <pre><code>$(document).mouseup(function (e) {     var container = $("#id1");     if (!container.is(e.target) // if the target of the click isn't the     container...         &amp;&amp; container.has(e.target).length === 0) // ... nor a descendant of the container     {         container.fadeOut();     }      var container2 = $("#id2");     if (!container2.is(e.target) // if the target of the click isn't the container...         &amp;&amp; container2.has(e.target).length === 0) // ... nor a descendant of the container     {         container2.fadeOut();     } } </code></pre>  <p>It basically checks, if the click happens outside the div and if so, the div fades out. However, I have like 15-20 to check and wonder, whether there is a shorter solution than copy&amp;paste for this.</p>  <p>Thanks!!!    </p>